<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-090-846  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 090 846.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  March 6 1989 v23 n9 p17(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC rules ATandamp;T must post rates.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Betts, Mitch.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Federal Communications Commission ruled that AT and T mustfully disclose its prices for the Federal TelecommunicationsSystem 2000.andP;  The company had argued that such disclosure wouldharm its position with its competitors.andP;  The FCC said that factorwas not sufficient to authorize a private tariff.andP;  The FTS-2000system will be built by AT and T as part of a recent contractaward that was shared with US Sprint Communications.andP;  AT and Tattempted to keep the tariff for the system private to keep USSprint from using the information when the contract comes up forbid again in 1992.andP;  MCI Communications, an unsuccessful bidder inthe negotiations, argued to the FCC that the unprecedented privatetariff would create a poor example.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (cases).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     TariffTelephone companiesDisclosureOrdersGovernment AgencyUnited States. Federal Communications Commission.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>